Although we interpret these deaths as linked to air pollution, we should note that air pollution acts in combination with other underlying diseases in the population that ultimately result in premature mortality or otherwise loss of expected remaining life. Deaths solely caused by air pollution, i.e. initiated by air pollution in isolation of other health risk factors, are likely to be lower. In the above expression, the cause-specific BM is specified based on GBD 2015 as7\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
