Pollution-related illness was calculated assuming that the percentage change in the number of cases of morbidity between scenarios were proportional to changes in the projected mortality. In particular, lost work days from air pollution-related illnesses were calculated using a morbidity-to-mortality multiplier of 547 avoided lost work days per avoided premature mortality, derived from the WHO-HRAPIE83 recommendations, based on earlier work84, and applied in the context of EU Clean Air Package85. More specifically, based on the supporting document86, we calculate a multiplier on the EU aggregate level:9\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
